        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Algorithmic Impact Assessment Scoping Methodology"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "An Algorithmic Impact Assessment (AIA) is a structured analysis of the potential harms an AI-assisted decision process could cause to individuals or groups. For Claude deployments, the AIA answers a specific question: given the way Claude is configured and integrated, what are the realistic adverse outcomes for real people, and are those outcomes proportionate to the value the system creates?"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Scoping is the first and most critical step of an AIA. A scope that is too narrow misses real impacts; a scope that is too broad produces a document so general it provides no actionable guidance. The methodology in this sub-subtopic produces a defensible scope that satisfies regulatory expectations from the EU AI Act, NIST AI RMF, and Canada's Directive on Automated Decision-Making."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Algorithmic Impact Assessment Scoping Decision Matrix",
          "title": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
